{% set host_addr = ansible_host | default(inventory_hostname) %}
{% set status_label = 'SUCCESS' if mikrotik_success | bool else 'FAILED' %}

+==============================================================================+
|                    MikroTik RouterOS — Deployment Summary                    |
+==============================================================================+

  Host ............ {{ inventory_hostname }} ({{ host_addr }})
  Success ......... {{ mikrotik_success | bool }} ({{ status_label }})

{% if mikrotik_warnings | length > 0 %}
  Warnings:
{% for warning in mikrotik_warnings %}
    - {{ warning }}
{% endfor %}
{% else %}
  Warnings ........ (none)
{% endif %}

+------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
|  Access (Markdown)                                                           |
+------------------------------------------------------------------------------+

#### On the server

| Service | Connection |
|---------|------------|
| SSH     | `ssh -p {{ mikrotik_ssh_port }} admin@127.0.0.1` |
| Web UI  | http://127.0.0.1:{{ mikrotik_web_port }} |
| Telnet  | `telnet 127.0.0.1 {{ mikrotik_telnet_port }}` |
| API     | `127.0.0.1:{{ mikrotik_api_port }}` |

#### Remote

| Service | Connection |
|---------|------------|
| SSH     | `ssh -p {{ mikrotik_ssh_port }} admin@{{ host_addr }}` |
| Web UI  | http://{{ host_addr }}:{{ mikrotik_web_port }} |

> First login: user **admin**, empty password (you will be prompted to set one).

> Open firewall ports **{{ mikrotik_ssh_port }}**, **{{ mikrotik_telnet_port }}**, **{{ mikrotik_web_port }}**, **{{ mikrotik_api_port }}** for external access.
